UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387886900295
AB  - The phenomenon of vertical trading, in which the center exports a good involving a high degree of processing which leads to economy-wide learning and the periphery exports a good which does not generate such effects, is formalized in a simple dynamic model of trade. It is shown that the periphery can ‘lose’ from such trade relations. Conditions under which this can occur are shown to involve parameters of the learning functions, and the ‘sizes’ of the two countries.
ER  - 
